Sentencas: Ce1-xLaxO2-delta (0 <= x <= 0.4) powders have been synthesized through a newly devised heat-treatment process in the co-precipitation method, and their sintering characteristics, electrical conductivity and thermal properties have been examined as potential electrolytes in the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Sintering characteristics, electrical conductivity and thermal properties of La-doped ceria powders

Sentencas: Sintering characteristics of the samples have a tendency to decrease with increasing dopant content of La.
Titulo: Sintering characteristics, electrical conductivity and thermal properties of La-doped ceria powders

Sentencas: A relative density >= 94% was obtained after heating at 1500 degrees C for 2h for Ce0.9La0.1O1.95 and at 1600 degrees C for 10h for Ce0.8La0.2O1.9.
Titulo: Sintering characteristics, electrical conductivity and thermal properties of La-doped ceria powders

Sentencas: Electrical conductivies at 500 degrees C and thermal expansion coefficients (50-500 degrees C) in air for the sintered samples were 3.48 x 10(-3) S/cm and 11.5 x 10(-6) C-1 for Ce0.9La0.1O1.95, and 3.71 X 10(-3) S/cm and 11.7 x 10(-6), C-1 for Ce0.8La0.2O1.9.
Titulo: Sintering characteristics, electrical conductivity and thermal properties of La-doped ceria powders
